<div class="calendaria chat-release">
  <div class="release-header">
    <i class="fa-solid fa-calendar"></i>
    <strong>{{localize "CALENDARIA.Release.Title" version=version}}</strong>
  </div>

  <div class="release-body">
    <p class="release-patreon">
      <strong><a href="https://www.patreon.com/3deathsaves" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><i
            class="fa-brands fa-patreon"></i> Now on Patreon!</a></strong>
    </p>

    <h4>New Features</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Each calendar can now define its own Cross-Calendar display format in the editor's Display tab, controlling
        how its dates appear when shown as equivalents on other calendars</li>
      <li>New "Week Starts On" option in the calendar editor's Weeks tab rotates the mini and big calendar grids so a
        chosen weekday appears in the first column, without altering the underlying weekday cycle</li>
      <li>On PF2e and SF2e worlds, calendars without a Luxon sync theme now auto-align their displayed time-of-day with
        the system world clock's starting time, so the Calendaria clock matches the core Foundry clock without affecting
        calendar math</li>
      <li>Short rests on dnd5e now advance world time independently of long rests, with a new Time-tab setting to choose
        Automatic (system-reported duration) or Fixed minutes (default 60)</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Bug Fixes</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Custom HUD format tokens with empty values (such as a missing canonical hour) now render as blank instead of
        leaking the literal token text</li>
      <li>Reordering months, weekdays, or seasons on older calendars no longer gets stuck swapping within the same
        group; existing calendars are migrated to stable random keys on load</li>
      <li>Cycle conditions on notes now show the correct stage list and stop breaking when cycles or stages are
        reordered, with old saved values still matching</li>
      <li>The condition builder on a note now uses that note's calendar instead of always defaulting to the active one
      </li>
      <li>Players without Big Calendar access now see a permission warning toast instead of a momentary dialog flash
        when triggering the show-calendar macro</li>
      <li>BigCal week view weekday labels now rotate with the Week Starts On setting so each column header matches its
        actual weekday</li>
      <li>Simple Calendar importer no longer misclassifies one-off dated notes as recurring festivals; festivals are
        only created for yearly-recurring or intercalary-anchored entries</li>
      <li>Simple Calendar imports now correctly remap month indices when intercalary months are stripped, so imported
        current dates and note dates land on the right Calendaria month</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Changes</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Fresh installs now boot with cinematic mode, weather/moon/event overlays, scene syncing, HUD weather FX, chat
        timestamp clock, weather auto-generation, and FXMaster integration off so a new world stays quiet until you opt
        in; the in-HUD calendar widget is now shown by default</li>
      <li>The per-scene "Disable Weather FX" checkbox is now a "Weather FX Override" dropdown with Inherit, On, and Off;
        existing disabled scenes are migrated automatically</li>
    </ul>

  </div>

  <a class="open-note" href="{{repoUrl}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
    <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-up-right-from-square"></i> {{localize "CALENDARIA.Release.ReleaseNotes"}}
  </a>
</div>
